"We analyzed HEALPix databases with nside = 1024; there-
fore, the effective pixel resolution is 3.′44 (Górski et al. 2005)
and, accordingly, the H(x, y) filter acts on a scale of 18′. The
FIR data, in comparison to the H i channel maps, are sensitivity
limited (see, e.g., Figs. 3 and 4 of Kalberla et al. 2016). To avoid
unnecessary noise amplification when deriving first and second
derivatives, we smoothed the Planck 857 GHz data to an effec-
tive resolution of 18′. Thus we matched the full width at half
maximum (FWHM) of the smoothing filter to the 5 pixels of the
grid used by the Hessian analysis. Such an adapted smoothing
leads to significant reduction of the uncertainties (see Sect. 2.3).
In Fig. 1 we display the resulting distribution of eigenvalues that
