"For the H i data we used Gaussian components from Kalberla
& Haud (2019) with a FWHM beamwidth of 14.′5 for the GASS
and 10.′8 for the EBHIS. In comparison to the FIR databases
there is a slight mismatch in spatial resolution but we intend to
analyze correlations between FIR emission and H i at the high-
est possible resolution. A smoothing would disable the use of
the Gaussian database since the fitting is a nonlinear process.
Our analysis is hierarchical in the sense that we always use the
857 GHz FIR data as a template to search for structures at other
frequencies. A slightly smaller FWHM width for the H i data
does not violate the Nyquist theorem since both databases are
on the same HEALPix grid. Tests with several different smooth-
ing kernels indicated anyway that the derived eigenvalues do not
depend critically on the smoothing kernel used."
